The topic comes up often, about why people in EQ decide to enjoin their characters in a relationship such as a marriage. This thread gives me an opportunity to expound on that a little bit.<br>
<br>
There are probably as many reasons as there are people playing EQ. Some do so because their characters are either married or in relationship in RL. Others because they have established a friendship and the marriage is a nice way of acknowledging that friendship. Others, yes, use EQ as a dating service and actively seek someone to get into a relationship...or whatever <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ... with. Still others *gasp* enjoy role playing, and develop stories that involve each other, of which marriage is one.<br>
<br>
Many of you know that my character was once married in game. In the case of the players behind Yaenna and Stallion (Yaenna's in game husband), we both enjoyed role playing, and for a long time our schedules were such that we could play together often. Joining the characters provided a rich opportunity to do both. <br>
<br>
For example, Stallion, being a Knight of Mithaniel Marr (a paladin) was sworn to avenge the taking of Freeport by the Freeport Militia. This meant killing the militia and being forever KOS in the E/W Freeport and E/W Commons areas. Yaenna, being a Soldier of Tunare and a priestess (druid), was vehemently opposed to killing sentient beings, of which at one time she considered the Freeport Militia <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . Not to mention that Freeport is a trade center, providing all the necessary goods for all her trade skills. Being KOS in Freeport was not something she was interested in being.<br>
<br>
Inside of role play it was exciting for me (the player) to watch how the player behind Stallion began to draw Yaenna into his story, eventually convincing her to align with him. As his wife, what choice would she have but to support him? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START >D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/grin.gif ALT=">D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  There were many sub plots to their relationship like that, and for a long while it was fun for both of us to create them and play them out. Besides,  Stallion was a character sworn to fight and protect, who better to protect than Yaenna? Yaenna was sworn to serve and to heal. Who better to serve and to heal than Stallion? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
As with all things however, role play relationships can come to a close. After months of role playing, it began to be obvious to the players behind Stallion and Yaenna that we weren't interested in continuing to role play the relationship. The characters COULD have gone on just pretending to be married and let it go at that, or simply drift away. Many many character relationship just simply dissolve with no explanation whatsoever. But for me, I play EQ to involve my character in a life. It's a made up life, true, but nevertheless, my characters have a history, and much (not all) of my fun is playing the character in keeping with that history. Not to mention that I don't care for loose ends. The relationship was built in role play, it made sense to me to dissolve it in role play, or at least with a story. Neither of us wanted to role play it, so I decided to write a story to explain the break up.<br>
<br>
As an aside, the dilemma of how to do that was a challenge for me, and one I enjoyed working out. These two characters were loyal to a fault. They would never simply abandon each other. A lot of possibilities existed, such as black magic or some evil force that intervened to cause them to part. But one day a story for an ending just came to me, and I wrote it down. It gave me closure on a role I had played out with vigor for many months. I enjoyed that phase of Yaenna's life, but it was only one phase. She's now on to bigger and better things!<br>
<br>
For anyone who's interested (it's a long read), the ending story can be found at:<br>
